docs.lead_paragraph: Mrs. Annie Kronman, who was attacked with a hatchet by some person or persons unknown in her flat at 266 West Thirty-fifth Street Monday afternoon, died in the Roosevelt Hospital shortly before 9 o'clock yesteray morning. It was realized from the moment she was taken there that she could not survive her wounds.

headline.main: MRS. ANNE KRONMAN DEAD; Woman Assaulted in Her Home Did Not Regain Consciousness. HUSBAND REMANDED IN COURT Said to Have Been Seen Issuing from House About the Time the Crime Was Committed.

docs.abstract: Assaulted with Hatchet in Her Home; Husband Arrested
